#: ../../library/locale.rst:26
msgid ""
"Exception raised when the locale passed to :func:`setlocale` is not "
"recognized."
msgstr ""
"ExceĂ§ĂŁo levantada quando a localidade passada para :func:`setlocale` nĂŁo ĂŠ "
"reconhecida."

#: ../../library/locale.rst:32
msgid ""
"If *locale* is given and not ``None``, :func:`setlocale` modifies the locale "
"setting for the *category*. The available categories are listed in the data "
"description below. *locale* may be a :ref:`string <locale_name>`, or a pair, "
"language code and encoding. An empty string specifies the user's default "
"settings. If the modification of the locale fails, the exception :exc:"
"`Error` is raised. If successful, the new locale setting is returned."
msgstr ""
"Se *locale* for fornecido e nĂŁo ``None``, :func:`setlocale` modifica a "
"configuraĂ§ĂŁo de locale para a *category*. As categorias disponĂ­veis estĂŁo "
"listadas na descriĂ§ĂŁo dos dados abaixo. *locale* pode ser uma :ref:`string "
"<locale_name>` ou um par, cĂłdigo de idioma e codificaĂ§ĂŁo. Uma string vazia "
"especifica as configuraĂ§Ăľes padrĂŁo do usuĂĄrio. Se a modificaĂ§ĂŁo da "
"localidade falhar, a exceĂ§ĂŁo :exc:`Error` ĂŠ levantada. Se for bem-sucedido, "
"a nova configuraĂ§ĂŁo de localidade serĂĄ retornada."

#: ../../library/locale.rst:39
msgid ""
"If *locale* is a pair, it is converted to a locale name using the locale "
"aliasing engine. The language code has the same format as a :ref:`locale "
"name <locale_name>`, but without encoding. The language code and encoding "
"can be ``None``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../library/locale.rst:45
msgid ""
"If *locale* is omitted or ``None``, the current setting for *category* is "
"returned."
msgstr ""
"Se *locale* for omitido ou ``None``, a configuraĂ§ĂŁo atual para *category* ĂŠ "
"retornada."

#: ../../library/locale.rst:48
msgid "Example::"
msgstr "Exemplo::"

#: ../../library/locale.rst:50
msgid ""
">>> import locale\n"
">>> loc = locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL)  # get current locale\n"
"# use German locale; name and availability varies with platform\n"
">>> locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, 'de_DE.UTF-8')\n"
">>> locale.strcoll('f\\xe4n', 'foo')  # compare a string containing an "
"umlaut\n"
">>> locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, '')   # use user's preferred locale\n"
">>> locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, 'C')  # use default (C) locale\n"
">>> locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, loc)  # restore saved locale"
msgstr ""

#: ../../library/locale.rst:59
msgid ""
